@4209  = ~This rogue is part acrobat, part duellist, and part wit: the epitome of charm and grace. Swashbucklers are seen by many as dandies, and they generally make poor thieves. But their skill with blades is not to be underestimated; it usually gets them out of trouble when charm fails.~
